{
  "texts": [
    "For larger trades we 'eat through' the order book.",
    "To buy a quantity of an asset, we buy each ask lot, in order from lowest price, until we fill our order.",
    "An analogous situation occurs when selling.",
    "This means that we end up paying more per share than the ask price when buying, or receiving less than the bid price when selling.",
    "This phenomenon is called market impact."
  ]
}